BBC Music magazine (November 2014)

ISSN: 0966-7180 | 102 pages | PDF


BBC MUSIC MAGAZINE is a must for anyone with a passion for classical music.  Classical music connoisseurs and new enthusiast alike will enjoy the fascinating features and reviews of over 120 new works in every issue, including sections on jazz and world music.

IN THE NOVEMBER ISSUE:

* In an exclusive interview, pianist Mitsuko Uchida reflects on her journey with the music of Mozart, Schumann and Beethoven;

* conductor Vasily Petrenko presents his in-depth guide to all 15 of Shostakovich's symphonies;

* Jeremy Pound explores the hoots and squawks of Richard Blackford's &quot;The Great Animal Orchestra&quot;;

* James Naughtie meets the brilliant Bach pianist, Angela Hewitt;

* and George Hall celebrates the life and work of operatic innovator Christoph Willibald Gluck.

